\begin_layout Standard
Overall for SMAZ, observed average compressed message lengths were all worse
 than the claimed range for English text, and in the case of Twitter messages
 much worse, with average compressed message lengths of 81.4% of the uncompressed
 message length.
 Thus, while effective in many instances, SMAZ elegantly small dictionary-based
 approach is not sufficiently robust in the face of Twitter type traffic.
\end_layout

